    "faq": {
      "type": "lsc-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is IPL?",
            "answer": "<p>IPL (Intense Pulsed Light) is a non-invasive light-based treatment used to reduce pigmentation, sun damage, redness and uneven skin tone. It works by delivering controlled pulses of light energy into the skin, targeting pigment and blood vessels without damaging surrounding tissue.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What skin concerns can IPL treat?",
            "answer": "<p>• Sun damage</p><p>• Age spots and pigmentation</p><p>• Freckles</p><p>• Redness and flushing</p><p>• Broken capillaries</p><p>• Uneven skin tone</p><p>• Rosacea-type symptoms</p><p>• Dull skin</p><p>A consultation will confirm whether IPL is suitable for your specific concern.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does IPL work?",
            "answer": "<p>IPL delivers broad-spectrum light energy into the skin. The light is absorbed by pigment (melanin) or blood vessels, which are then naturally broken down and cleared by the body over time. This results in a clearer, more even complexion.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does IPL differ from laser treatments?",
            "answer": "<p>Unlike traditional lasers that use a single wavelength of light, IPL uses broad-spectrum light. This allows it to treat multiple concerns such as pigmentation and redness in the same session.</p><p>Your clinician will recommend the most appropriate treatment for your skin type and concern.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is IPL safe?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. IPL is considered a safe and well-established treatment when performed using medical-grade equipment in a clinical environment. A consultation and, where appropriate, a test patch are carried out before treatment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is IPL safe for all skin types?",
            "answer": "<p>IPL is generally most suitable for lighter skin tones with pigmentation or redness concerns. It may not be appropriate for darker skin tones due to the way light interacts with melanin. A full assessment will determine suitability.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_7": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there any downtime?",
            "answer": "<p>Downtime is typically minimal. You may experience:</p><p>• Mild redness</p><p>• Slight warmth</p><p>• Temporary darkening of pigmentation</p><p>These effects usually settle within a few days.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_8": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can IPL treat Rosacea?",
            "answer": "<p>IPL can help reduce visible redness and broken capillaries associated with certain types of rosacea. However, suitability depends on your individual skin condition and will be assessed during consultation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_9": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What should I avoid after IPL?",
            "answer": "<p>You should avoid:</p><p>• Direct sun exposure</p><p>• Tanning</p><p>• Retinoids and strong exfoliants for several days</p><p>• Heat treatments such as saunas or hot tubs for 24–48 hours</p><p>Strict sun protection is essential.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_10": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do results last?",
            "answer": "<p>Results can be long-lasting when combined with good sun protection and skincare. Maintenance sessions may be recommended depending on your skin type and lifestyle.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_11": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does IPL hurt?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients describe IPL as a quick, warm flicking sensation on the skin. Discomfort is usually brief and well tolerated.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_12": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "When will I see results?",
            "answer": "<p>Some improvement may be visible after the first session. Pigmented areas often darken slightly before flaking away within 3–7 days. Results continue to improve gradually with each session.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_13": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many sessions will I need?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients require a course of 3–5 treatments spaced approximately 4 weeks apart for optimal results. The exact number depends on the severity of pigmentation or redness and your skin type.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_14": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What payment options do you offer?",
            "answer": "<p>We offer flexible payment options to make your treatment as convenient as possible. You can choose to pay per single session or pay in full for a course of treatments for better overall value. We accept card, cash, and bank transfer in clinic.</p><p>For added flexibility, we also offer 0% finance through Klarna, allowing you to spread the cost into manageable instalments with a range of payment options available, subject to eligibility.</p><p>If you’re unsure which option is best for you, our team will be happy to guide you.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_15": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What can IPL treat?",
            "answer": "<p>IPL can treat a wide variety of concerns including thread veins, spider veins, sun damage, pigmentation, rosacea, and age spots.<br/><br/>It can also improve overall skin tone and texture by stimulating collagen production.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_16": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do I need a patch test before starting IPL?",
            "answer": "<p>You must have a patch test before you can have IPL as per our insurance requirements. Once you've had a patch test you can come back for your first session 48 hours later.<br/><br/>This ensures your treatment is both safe and highly effective.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_17": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "I would like to speak to someone before I book my treatment, how is best to do this?",
            "answer": "<p>If you would like to speak to someone please do one of the below.<br/><br/>- Use the enquiry button.<br/><br/>- Contact us via email at info@laserskinclinics.co.uk<br/><br/>- Call us during opening hours on 01902 256667<br/><br/>- Send us a WhatsApp by clicking the WhatsApp button on the website.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_18": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is your cancellation policy?",
            "answer": "<p>Cancellations up to 24 hours before your appointment will receive a full refund or can be rescheduled.<br/><br/>Any cancellations on the day can be rescheduled but will not be refunded.<br/><br/>If you do not show to your appointment you will not receive a refund or a reschedule. Please note that we offer email and text appointment reminders right up until 24 hours before your appointment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_19": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What happens if I want to book a course?",
            "answer": "<p>If you want to book a course you can do this at the clinic after your first session. Any discount for booking a course will also he applied.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_20": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who is IPL suitable for?",
            "answer": "<p>IPL is suitable for most skin types and is ideal for individuals looking to treat redness, pigmentation, or vascular concerns without downtime.<br/><br/>A patch test is always carried out beforehand to confirm suitability.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_21": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many sessions will I need?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients require a course of 3 to 6 sessions spaced 3 to 4 weeks apart for best results.<br/><br/>Your practitioner will recommend the ideal number of sessions based on your skin condition and goals.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_22": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "When will I see results?",
            "answer": "<p>Many clients notice improvement after the first session, with continued enhancement as pigmentation fades and redness reduces over the course of treatments.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_23": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does IPL hurt?",
            "answer": "<p>The treatment is generally comfortable.<br/><br/>You may feel a mild, warm snapping sensation during each light pulse, similar to a light elastic flick on the skin.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
